  "location": "Melbourne",
  "event_preview": "Albert Park Circuit is measured at 5.278 km (3.280 mi) and hosts FIA Formula 3 as a support series during the Australian Grand Prix weekend. For F3 machinery, the circuit presents a significant challenge: limited downforce levels make the high-speed sweepers through Turns 9–12 particularly demanding, while the tight Turn 3 hairpin remains the primary overtaking opportunity. The semi-permanent nature of the track means grip evolves dramatically across the weekend, making qualifying pace difficult to predict. The official F3 race lap record is 1:34.405, set by Grégoire Saucy for ART Grand Prix during the 2023 feature race, while the overall fastest F3 lap - a 1:33.025 - was set in qualifying by Gabriel Bortoleto for Trident, also in 2023.",
